# Tech Stack — Version Pinning

- Language: TypeScript (strict mode, no `any` types)
- Framework: Vite + React 18 (functional components + hooks only)
- State Management: React `useReducer` — no Redux, no Zustand, no MobX
- Touch/Gestures: `@use-gesture/react`
- Animation: CSS Transitions + Web Animations API (`element.animate()`)
- Audio: Web Audio API (synthesized oscillators, zero audio files)
- Testing: Vitest + fast-check (property-based testing for engine)
- E2E Testing: Cypress (2 critical paths only)
- Deployment: Vercel + `vite-plugin-pwa`
- Package Manager: npm

## Banned Libraries

- Do NOT use Framer Motion — use Web Animations API instead (bundle size)
- Do NOT use Redux, Zustand, Jotai, or any external state library
- Do NOT use LangChain or LlamaIndex on the client
- Do NOT use jQuery or Lodash
- Do NOT add audio files — all sounds must be Web Audio API synthesized
- Do NOT add Google Analytics, Mixpanel, Segment, or any tracking scripts
- Do NOT add any CDN dependencies that set cookies

## Bundle Budget

Total JS bundle (gzipped) must stay under 150 KB. Before adding any dependency, check its size with `npx bundlephobia <package>`. If it pushes the bundle over budget, find an alternative or implement it yourself.
